ealpython.com%2Fwrite-for-us%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20WPHub%20(up%20to%20%24200)%5Cn%5CnWPHub%20pays%20up%20to%20%24200%20per%20article.%20They%20publish%20tutorials%20about%20WordPress.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wphub.com%2Fwrite-for-us%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Tutorialspoint%20(up%20to%20%24500)%5Cn%5CnTutorialspoint%20pays%20up%20to%20%24500%20per%20article.%20You%20can%20choose%20from%20specified%20topics%20or%20write%20about%20any%20technical%20topic.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tutorialspoint.com%2Fabout%2Ftutorials_writing.htm).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Fauna%20(up%20to%20%24500)%5Cn%5CnFauna%20pays%20up%20to%20%24500%20per%20article.%20They%20provide%20topics%20to%20write%20about.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Ffauna.com%2Fblog%2Fwrite-with-fauna).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Smashing%20Magazine%20(up%20to%20%24250)%5Cn%5CnSmashing%20Magazine%20takes%20tutorials%2C%20guides%20and%20case%20studies.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smashingmagazine.com%2Fwrite-for-us%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20GitLab%20(up%20to%20%24200)%5Cn%5CnGitlab%20pays%20up%20to%20%24200%20per%20article.%20They%20take%20articles%20that%20help%20you%20get%20better%20at%20development.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fabout.gitlab.com%2Fcommunity%2Fwriters%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Linode%20(up%20to%20%24300%2B)%5Cn%5CnLinode%20pays%20a%20minimum%20of%20%24300%20per%20article%20and%20also%20pays%20%24100%20for%20an%20existing%20article.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linode.com%2Flp%2Fwrite-for-linode%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20CircleCI%20(up%20to%20%24300)%5Cn%5CnCircleCI%20pays%20up%20to%20%24300%20per%20article.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fcircleci.com%2Fblog%2Fguest-writer-program%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20TypingDNA%20(up%20to%20%24500)%5Cn%5CnTypingDNA%20pays%20up%20to%20%24500%20per%20article.%20You're%20expected%20to%20write%20articles%20related%20to%20TypingDNA.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.typingdna.com%2Fguest-author-program).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Draft%20(up%20to%20%24500)%5Cn%5CnDraft%20pays%20up%20to%20%24500%20per%20article.%20They%20provide%20topics%20to%20choose%20from.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fdraft.dev%2F%3Futm_source%3Dcfpland_newsletter%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_campaign%3DWeekly%2BEmail%26utm_term%3D2021-03-11T09%253A06%253A28.139Z%23write).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20SitePoint%20(up%20to%20%24100)%5Cn%5CnSitePoint%20pays%20%24100%20or%20more.%20%5BApply%20here%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sitepoint.com%2Fwrite-for-us).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Arctype%20(up%20to%20%24100%2B)%5Cn%5CnArctype%20pays%20up%20to%20%24100%2B%20per%20article%20and%20takes%20articles%20about%20SQL%2C%20Databases%2C%20and%20Daya%20analysis.%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20Publications%20Where%20You%20Can%20Write%20Articles%20to%20Share%20with%20the%20Community%20(Not%20Paid)%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20FreeCodeCamp%5Cn%5CnfreeCodeCamp%20publishes%20articles%20about%20web%20development%2C%20data%20science%2C%20DevOps%2C%20Machine%20Learning%20and%20AI%2C%20math%2C%20learning%20to%20code%2C%20job%20searching%2C%20and%20more.%20You%20can%20apply%20to%20become%20an%20author%2C%20and%20if%20you're%20a%20good%20fit%2C%20you'll%20be%20able%20to%20set%20up%20an%20account.%20%5BHere's%20how%20to%20apply%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freecodecamp.org%2Fnews%2Fhow-to-write-for-freecodecamp%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Dev.to%5CnDev.to%20is%20like%20your%20personal%20blog%20and%20you%20can%20post%20any%20article%20you%20want%20as%20long%20as%20it%20abides%20by%20the%20community%20rules%20and%20regulations.%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Hashnode%5CnHashnode%20is%20a%20personal%20blog%20with%20a%20touch%20of%20community.%5Cn%5CnHow%20do%20you%20feel%20after%20checking%20out%20this%20list%3F%5Cn%5CnWell%2C%20if%20you're%20just%20like%20me%2C%20I%20wanted%20some%20more%20guidance%20-%20I%20wanted%20to%20know%20how%20to%20%5C%22get%20in%5C%22%20and%20start%20making%20money.%5Cn%5CnIf%20you%20feel%20the%20same%2C%20don't%20worry%2C%20I%20will%20show%20you%20how%20to%20get%20yourself%20in%20even%20if%20you're%20a%20total%20novice.%20Just%20keep%20on%20reading!%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20Publications%20that%20Pay%20You%20For%20Non-Technical%20Articles.%5Cn%5CnIf%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20belong%20to%20tech%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20other%20publications%20that%20pay%20you%20to%20write%20articles%20about%20fashion%2C%20food%2C%20health%20and%20others.%20%5Cn%5Cn%5BGet%20Paid%20to%20Write%20Articles%3A%2017%20Magazines%20That%20Pay%20%24500%20or%20More%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fthewritelife.com%2Fget-paid-to-write-articles%2F).%5Cn%5Cn%5BClick%20to%20download%20100%2B%20publications%20to%20write%20articles%20for%20(by%20writerhelpwanted.com%5D(https%3A%2F%2Fpdfhost.io%2Fv%2FtEdkl.fHg_102WebsitesThatPay)%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20What%20to%20Do%20Before%20You%20Start%20Writing%5Cn%5CnYou%20just%20need%20to%20say%20%5C%22Open%20Sesame%5C%22%20to%20get%20in%20(%F0%9F%A4%AA).%20Are%20you%20in%20after%20saying%20that%3F%20Oh%2C%20never%20mind!%5Cn%5CnIt%20might%20be%20intimidating%20having%20to%20apply%20to%20these%20platforms%20in%20order%20to%20write%20paid%20articles.%20They%20care%20a%20lot%20about%20quality%2C%20of%20course%2C%20and%20only%20want%20to%20publish%20articles%20that%20are%20suitable%20for%20their%20audiences.%5Cn%5CnSo%20you%20have%20to%20position%20yourself%20as%20someone%20who%20can%20deliver%20value%20to%20their%20audience.%20And%20let's%20be%20real.%20Why%20should%20they%20pay%20you%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20when%20they%20can%20get%20someone%20to%20write%20similar%20articles%20for%20less%20than%20%2430%20on%20Fiverr%3F%20You%20must%20be%20able%20to%20provide%20value%20tailored%20to%20their%20audience.%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20%F0%9F%94%B4%20Doing%20the%20job%20before%20getting%20the%20job.%5Cn%5CnI%20assume%20you%20have%20never%20written%20paid%20articles%20before%2C%20but%20that%20you're%20good%20at%20writing%20and%20programming.%20Fine!%20So%20you%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20write%20clearly%20and%20well%2C%20like%20someone%20a%20publication%20would%20want%20as%20a%20writer.%20%5Cn%5CnThe%20reality%20is%20that%20they%20don't%20really%20care%20about%20you.%20Why%20should%20they%3F%20They%20mostly%20care%20about%20their%20businesses%20and%20audience.%5Cn%5CnThen%2C%20what%20would%20you%20do%3F%20You%20need%20to%20write%20at%20least%20three%20articles.%20The%20articles%20must%20be%20good%20enough%20to%20get%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20platforms%20that%20pay%20for%20articles.%20The%20question%20now%20is%20how%20will%20you%20write%20such%20amazing%20articles%3F%20Yeah%2C%20this%20is%20the%20magic%20--%5C%22Learn%20from%20the%20best%2C%20copy%20from%20the%20best%20and%20apply%20your%20own%20style%5C%22.%5Cn%5CnThis%20is%20how%20to%20do%20it%3F%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Identify%20six%20platforms%5CnYou%20need%20to%20first%20identify%20six%20platforms%20you%20want%20to%20write%20for.%20I%20call%20this%20technique%20%5C%22The%20Rule%20of%20Six%5C%22.%20Let's%20use%20the%20platforms%20below%20as%20a%20case%20study.%5Cn%5Cn%E2%97%BDwww.freecodecamp.org%2Fnews%5Cn%5Cn%E2%97%BDwww.smashingmagazine.com%5Cn%5Cn%E2%97%BDwww.logrocket.com%2Fblogs%5Cn%5Cn%E2%97%BDwww.auth0.com%5Cn%5Cn%E2%97%BDwww.clubhouse.io%5Cn%5Cn%E2%97%BDwww.twilio.com%5Cn%5CnWhy%20do%20I%20need%20six%20platforms%20again%3F%5Cn%5CnYou%20need%20to%20study%20what%20is%20considered%20acceptable%20by%20some%20of%20the%20platforms%20you%20want%20to%20write%20for.%20Checking%20these%20six%20platforms%20will%20expose%20you%20to%20the%20best%20writers%20in%20the%20industry.%5Cn%5CnWhat%20are%20we%20checking%20on%20the%20platforms%3F%5Cn%5CnYou%20want%20to%20check%20six%20authors%2C%20six%20writing%20styles%20and%20six%20topics.%5Cn%5CnTo%20make%20it%20easy%2C%20pick%20a%20topic%20from%20an%20author%20from%20each%20of%20the%20six%20platforms%20above.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20can%20pick%20an%20article%20from%20FreeCodeCamp%D8%8C%20one%20from%20SmashingMagazine%20and%20one%20from%20each%20of%20the%20rest.%5Cn%5CnMake%20sure%20the%20articles%20selected%20are%20about%20the%20topics%20you're%20good%20at%20because%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20discover%20the%20gap%20in%20your%20style%2C%20skills%20and%20knowledge%20by%20dealing%20with%20what%20you're%20also%20good%20at.%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Choosing%20your%20style%5Cn%5CnHonestly%2C%20I%20didn't%20choose%20my%20style%20with%20this%20process%20consciously%20but%20when%20I%20paid%20attention%20to%20why%20I%20write%20or%20talk%20the%20way%20I%20do%2C%20I%20discovered%20the%20process%20I%20have%20been%20explaining%20to%20you.%5Cn%5CnSo%2C%20you%20might%20have%20had%20a%20certain%20writing%20style%20already.%20By%20that%2C%20I%20mean%20it%20is%20not%20necessary%20to%20choose%20another%20writing%20style%20once%20you%20have%20a%20style%20already.%5Cn%5CnFor%20example%2C%20I%20don't%20try%20to%20adopt%20anybody's%20style%20but%20I%20adapt%20different%20writing%20styles%20from%20amazing%20authors%20and%20always%20allow%20my%20inner%20thought%20process%20to%20reflect%20to%20add%20a%20touch%20of%20humanity.%5Cn%5CnYou%20too%20can%20improve%20your%20writing%20styles%20with%20everything%20you%20have%20learned%20from%20others%20and%20that%20is%20fine.%20We%20are%20all%20learning%20from%20one%20another.%5Cn%5CnIf%20you're%20yet%20to%20have%20an%20amazing%20writing%20style%20you%20love%2C%20you%20can%20take%20your%20time%2C%20like%20a%20week%2C%20less%20than%20a%20week%20or%20more%20to%20read%20the%20articles%20you%20have%20gathered%20and%20develop%20your%20writing%20style%20with%20whatever%20you%20learn%20from%20the%20writing%20styles%20of%20the%20authors%20you%20have%20selected.%5Cn%5CnHonestly%2C%20it%20is%20best%20to%20adopt%20the%20general%20technical%20writing%20style%20because%20it%20will%20help%20you%20avoid%20unnecessary%20rejections.%20But%20for%20me%2C%20I%20do%20what%20makes%20me%20happy.%5Cn%5CnThen%2C%20what%20next%3F%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20What%20do%20you%20have%20to%20offer%3F%5Cn%5CnNobody%20knows%20whether%20you're%20an%20amazing%20writer%20or%20not%20until%20they%20see%20your%20write-up.%20So%2C%20you%20have%20to%20write%20some%20amazing%20articles%20to%20showcase%20your%20skills.%5Cn%5CnSo...%5Cn%5CnPick%20three%20topics%20out%20of%20the%20six%20topics%20you%20have%20identified%20earlier.%20Make%20sure%20the%20three%20topics%20you%20pick%20are%20the%20ones%20you%20know%20about%20the%20most%20among%20the%20selected%20topics.%5Cn%5CnThen%2C%20you%20need%20to%20write%20an%20article%20for%20each%20of%20the%20topics.%20Don't%20try%20to%20be%20in%20a%20hurry%20to%20finish%20all%20the%20articles%20but%20make%20sure%20you%20take%20your%20time%20to%20write%20each%20of%20the%20articles%20with%20the%20best%20of%20your%20writing%20skills.%5Cn%5CnAs%20far%20as%20I%20am%20concerned%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20is%20bad%20if%20it%20takes%20you%203%20to%204%20months%20or%201%20to%202%20days%20to%20write%20the%20three%20articles.%20What%20matters%20most%20is%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20articles.%5Cn%5CnHey!%20How%20can%20I%20write%20the%20articles%3F%5Cn%5CnIt%20is%20not%20rocket%20science.%20You%20just%20have%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20the%20work.%20You%20can%20use%20the%20approach%20I%20called%20%5C%22PROT%5C%22.%5Cn%5CnThese%20are%20the%20steps%20to%20follow%3A%5Cn%5CnPick%20three%20topics%20out%20of%20the%20six%20topics%3B%20then%20pick%20a%20topic%20from%20the%20three%20topics%20you%20have%20selected%20(6-3-1).%20This%20is%20what%20I%20mean.%20You%20need%20to%20identify%20six%20topics%20you%20can%20write%20about%2C%20narrow%20it%20down%20to%20three%20topics%20and%20pick%20a%20final%20topic%20to%20write%20about%20from%20the%20three%20selected%20topics.%20%5Cn%5CnDoing%20this%20helps%20you%20choose%20interesting%20topics.%20It%20could%20be%20very%20useful%20to%20identify%20a%20great%20topic.%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%5CnResearch%20the%20topic%20further%20and%20make%20sure%20you%20check%20all%20of%20the%20best%20articles%20on%20the%20topic.%5Cn%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%5CnCreate%20an%20outline%20for%20your%20writing.%20Map%20out%20all%20its%20parts%20to%20aids%20writing%20flow.%20%5Cn%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%20%5CnTry%20to%20write%20an%20article%20that%20beats%20all%20the%20best%20articles%20you%20have%20seen%20on%20the%20topic.%5Cn%5CnThat%20is%20the%20basic%20way%20to%20go%20about%20it%20but%20it%20is%20easier%20said%20than%20done.%5Cn%5CnThen%2C%20what%20next%3F%5Cn%5CnYou%20can%20share%20the%20first%20three%20articles%20on%20your%20personal%20blog%20or%20platforms%20with%20no%20entry%20barrier%20like%20dev.to%20and%20hashnode.com%5Cn%5CnBy%20doing%20this%2C%20you%20position%20yourself%20as%20an%20experienced%20technical%20writer%20that%20any%20platform%20would%20want%20as%20a%20writer.%5Cn%5CnHurrayyyyy!%5Cn%5CnYou're%20now%20an%20experienced%20technical%20writer.%5Cn%5CnWhat%20next%3F%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%20%F0%9F%94%B4%20How%20to%20get%20in%5Cn%5CnIt%20is%20time%20to%20get%20in.%20Below%20is%20the%20step%20by%20step%20approach%20to%20follow%3A%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Step%201%5CnResearch%20the%20interests%20of%20each%20of%20the%20platforms%20you%20want%20to%20write%20for.%5Cn%5CnFor%20instance%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20know%20about%20what%20it%20takes%20to%20write%20for%20FreeCodeCamp.%20The%20best%20place%20to%20know%20that%20is%20through%20Freecodecamp.%20So%20you%20have%20to%20research%20and%20know%20what%20they%20expect.%20You%20could%20google%20%5C%22write%20for%20us%20freecodecamp%5C%22.%5Cn%5CnFor%20Smashing%20Magazine%2C%20you%20could%20google%20%5C%22write%20for%20us%20smashing%20magazine%5C%22.%20In%20short%2C%20you%20could%20find%20necessary%20information%20about%20any%20publication%20you%20want%20by%20googling%20%5C%22write%20for%20us%20%2B%20companyName%5C%22.%5Cn%5CnDon't%20assume%20you%20can%20approach%20all%20of%20them%20the%20same%20way.%20You%20have%20to%20approach%20them%20based%20on%20their%20stated%20requirements%20or%20interests.%5Cn%5CnWait%3A%20Can%20I%20send%20you%20some%20stones%20from%20Nigeria%20for%20breakfast%3F%5Cn%5CnOh!%20Do%20you%20say%20%5C%22I%20am%20not%20interested%20in%20eating%20stone%5C%22%3F%20You%20see!%20We%20all%20have%20preferences.%20So%20give%20them%20what%20they%20want%20too.%5Cn%5CnResearch%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20publication%20you%20want%20to%20write%20for.%20It%20is%20very%20important%20because%20it%20determines%20whether%20you%20will%20be%20accepted%20or%20not.%5Cn%5Cn%23%23%23%20Step%202%5CnIt%20is%20time%20to%20apply.%20After%20checking%20most%20of%20the%20publications%20listed%20in%20this%20article%2C%20I%20realized%20the%20publications%20approach%20this%20application%20in%20two%20major%20ways.%5Cn%5CnSome%20ask%20you%20to%20give%20them%20your%20name%2C%20social%20media%20username%2C%20email%20and%20bio%2C%20for%20example%2C%20FreeCodeCamp.%5Cn%5CnYou%20can%20use%20below%20as%20a%20template%20to%20craft%20your%20own%20bio%3A%5Cn%5CnIn%20your%20bio%2C%20indicate%20your%20core%20interest%20first%20as%20in%3A%5Cn%5CnI%20am%20Ayobami%20Ogundiran%2C%20a%20software%20developer%20who%20loves%20helping%20those%20who%20are%20struggling%20to%20understand%20and%20build%20projects%20with%20JavaScript.%5Cn%5CnThen%20add%20your%20work%20experience%20(if%20any)%20as%20in%3A%20I%20have%20worked%20with%20%5Bcompany%20name%5D%20as%20a%20%5Bjob%20title%5D%2C%5Bcompany%20name%5D%20as%20a%20%5Bjob%20title%5D%20and%20%5Bcompany%20name%5D%20as%20a%20%5Bjob%20title%5D.%5Cn%5CnThere%20are%20some%20other%20platforms%2C%20such%20as%20Smashing%20Magazine%2C%20that%20want%20you%20to%20send%20the%20outline%20of%20the%20article%20you%20want%20to%20write%20to%20them%2C%20your%20name%2C%20email%20and%20bio.%5Cn%5CnThat%20means%20you%20have%20to%20also%20write%20an%20outline.%20But%20how%20do%20you%20write%20such%20an%20outline%3F%5Cn%5CnListen%2C%20this%20article%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20teach%20how%20to%20write%20an%20outline%20but%20I%20will%20give%20you%20an%20example%20you%20can%20learn%20from.%5Cn%5CnHere%20is%20the%20outline%20of%20Image%20To%20Text%20Conversion%20With%20React%20And%20Tesseract.js%20(OCR)%20I%20wrote%20for%20Smashing%20Magazine.%5Cn%5CnHeadline%3A%20Image%20To%20Text%20Conversion%20With%20React%20And%20Tesseract.js%20(OCR)%5Cn%5CnA.%20Introduction%5Cn%5Cna)%20Data%20as%20the%20backbone%20of%20any%20software%20application.%5Cn%5Cnb)%20Inability%20to%20extract%20texts%20from%20an%20image%20as%20a%20limition%20to%20data%20processing.%5Cn%5Cnc)%20OCR%20as%20a%20solution.%5Cn%5CnB.%20What%20is%20OCR%3F%5Cn%5Cna)%20What%20does%20OCR%20stand%20for%3F%20Optical%20Character%20Recognition%5Cn%5Cnb)%20Meaning%20of%20Optical%20Character%20Recognition.%5Cn%5CnC.%20Evolution%20of%20OCR.%20Optical%20Character%20Recognition%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20several%20inventions%20but%20below%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20have%20great%20impacts%20on%20OCR.%5Cn%5Cna)%20Optophone%20was%20developed%20to%20convert%20a%20printed%20page%20to%20produce%20tones%20that%20are%20corresponded%20to%20specific%20letters%20or%20character%20on%20the%20page.%5Cn%5Cnb)%20Gismo%20was%20developed%20to%20recognise%20all%2026%20letters%20of%20the%20Latin%20alphabet%20as%20produce%20by%20a%20standard%20type-writer%5Cn%5Cnc)%20CCD%20flatbed%20scanner%20introduced%20the%20first%20omni-present%20optical%20character%20recognition%20system%20that%20could%20recognise%20any%20fonts.%5Cn%5Cnd)%20Newton%20MessagePad%20was%20designed%20to%20recognise%20handwritten%20characters.%5Cn%5Cne)%20Tesseract%20intruduces%20neural%20networks%20to%20OCR%20to%20recognise%20patterns%20for%20themselves.%5Cn%5CnD.%20Why%20use%20OCR%3F%5Cn%5Cna).%20Regulations%20-%20It%20makes%20it%20possible%20to%20regulate%20media%20content.%20E.g%20Hiding%20sensitive%20media%20contents%20like%20on%20Twitterand%20regulation%20of%20amount%20of%20texts%20on%20Facebook%20ads%20images.%5Cn%5Cnb).%20Searchability%20-%20It%20makes%20images%20or%20printed%20documents%20searchable.%5Cn%5Cnc).%20Accessibility%20-%20It%20can%20provide%20useful%20information%20from%20an%20image%20to%20a%20screen-reader.%5Cn%5Cnd).%20Data%20processing%20automation%20-%20Pin%20on%20a%20card%20or%20QR%20code%20can%20be%20extracted%20and%20processed.%5Cn%5Cne).%20Digitalization%20of%20printed%20materials%20-%20It%20makes%20it%20easy%20to%20convert%20printed%20documents%20to%20digital%20ones%20to%20store%20or%20edit%20them.%5Cn%5CnE.%20Dos%20and%20Donts%20of%20OCR.%5Cn%5CnDo%20pre-process%20images%20for%20accurate%20results.%5CnDo%20think%20about%20security%5CnHandle%20exceptions%5CnDon't%20take%20all%20file%20formats%20as%20Tesseract%20cannot%20handle%20all%20file%20formats.%5CnF.%20What%20is%20Tesseract.js%3F%5Cn%5CnTesseract.js%20is%20a%20JavaScript%20libray%20that%20compiles%20the%20original%20Tesseract%20from%20C%20to%20JavaScript%20WebAssembly%20thereby%20making%20OCR%20accessible%20in%20the%20browser.%5Cn%5CnG.%20What%20we%20will%20build%20-%20an%20amazon%20giftcard-pin%20extractor.%20We%20will%20build%20a%20simple%20application%20that%20extracts%20the%20pin%20code%20of%20a%20scanned%20amazon%20giftcard.%5Cn%5Cna)%20Image%20Pre-processing%5Cn%5Cn1.%20Binarization%20-%20Converting%20the%20pixels%20of%20an%20image%20to%20either%20black%20and%20white.%5Cn%5Cn2.%20Noise%20Removal%20-%20Removing%20small%20dots%2Fpatches%20of%20high%20intensity%20in%20an%20image%20by%20blurring%20it.%5Cn%5Cn3.%20Thinning%20and%20Skeletonization%20-%20It%20is%20used%20to%20create%20a%20uniform%20width%20of%20strokes%20in%20hand%20written%20documents%20because%20handwritten%20texts%20have%20different%20strokes%20as%20different%20writers%20write%20differently.%5Cn%5Cn4.%20Skew%20Correction%20-%20A%20scanned%20document%20maybe%20be%20skewed%20a%20bit%20and%20it%20is%20corrected%20by%20re-aligning%20the%20skewed%20content.%5Cn%5Cnb).%20Converting%20a%20pre-processed%20image%20to%20texts%5Cn%5Cnc).%20Extracting%20a%20certain%20string%20of%20number%20(pin)%20from%20the%20text%5Cn%5Cnd).%20Matching%20the%20pin%20for%20confirmatione).%20Desplaying%20a%